This investigation comes amidst a safety crisis that has tarnished Boeing's reputation following a mid-air panel incident on a 737 MAX plane on January 5.
title: Boeing faces fresh safety scrutiny amid whistleblower claims

description: Garcetti, while speaking at the 'Impact & Innovation: 25 Years of Making Development a Ground Reality' event in Delhi on Wednesday, said, "If you want to see the future, come to India. If you want to feel the future, come to India. If you want to work on the future, come to India. I have the great privilege of being able to do that every single day as the leader of the US Mission."
title: 'Come to India': Garcetti's message to those who want to see future

description: In a significant victory, Jagjit Pavadia of India was re-elected to the International Narcotics Control Board (INCB), getting the highest number of votes in a highly competitive election conducted by the UN Economic and Social Council (ECOSOC). “Today, India's nominee Ms Jagjit Pavadia has been re-elected to the International Narcotics Control Board at elections held in New York, for the term 2025-2030,” External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar said in a post on X Tuesday. He noted that India secured the highest number of votes amongst all elected member states to the Board.
title: India's Jagjit Pavadia re-elected to International Narcotics Control Board

description: Three family members died trying to save a cat in an abandoned well in Ahmednagar. Despite rescue attempts, only one could be saved. Specialized equipment was used in the recovery process.
title: 5 of Maharashtra family die in bid to save cat in abandoned well

description: MS Dhoni, who retired from Test cricket in 2014, continues to inspire fans with his presence on the field. A viral video featuring his wife, Sakshi Dhoni, provides insight into their personal dynamics, reminiscing about Dhoni's unexpected retirement and the sacrifices and joys of being married to the World Cup-winning cricketing icon.
title: Viral video: Sakshi reveals insights behind Dhoni's Test retirement

description: BCCI is mulling increasing IPL player retentions to enhance team stability. Franchises will push for larger retained player numbers and higher salary cap. Challenges faced by Delhi Capitals and RCB post-auction to be discussed at upcoming meeting. According to sources, the board has invited all 10 franchise owners for a meeting in Ahmedabad next week.
title: IPL Mega Auction: BCCI to discuss increasing player retention

description: US President Joe Biden said Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's Gaza policy was a "mistake" and urged Israel to call for a ceasefire, in an interview aired Tuesday. In the call on Thursday, Biden had said Israel must led more aid in immediately and protect civilians, while urging Netanyahu to "empower his negotiators" to quickly reach a ceasefire with Hamas.
title: President Biden says Netanyahu making 'mistake' on Gaza

description: US President Joe Biden welcomed Japanese Prime Minister Fumio Kishida to the White House Tuesday, kicking off a state visit featuring a major upgrade in defense ties against a resurgent China. Kishida, 66, the first Japanese leader to receive full honors from a US president since Shinzo Abe in 2015, arrived on Tuesday night at the White House with his wife Yuko.
title: Biden welcomes Japan PM for state visit with eye on China

description: Arizona to ban abortion except to save a woman's life, with no exceptions for rape or incest. The state Supreme Court's ruling will likely have significant repercussions, impacting access to legal abortion and leading to potential desperate measures by individuals seeking abortion.
title: Arizona can enforce law criminalizing nearly all abortions, court says
